        <div class="text-center" style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
            <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>

        <div>
            <details class="faq-item" open>
                <summary>What if my ERC filer is no longer in business?<span>&#8595;</span></summary>
                <p class="faq-answer">Many businesses are in this position. We can step in as your successor representative, reconstruct your file, and provide the defense your original filer cannot.</p>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Why do I need professional representation?<span>&#8595;</span></summary>
                <p class="faq-answer">The IRS examines ERC claims with intense scrutiny. Professional representation ensures your responses are properly framed, your documentation is complete, and your rights are protected throughout the process.</p>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Do I have to pay back the credit if audited?<span>&#8595;</span></summary>
                <p class="faq-answer">Only if the IRS successfully challenges your eligibility. Our goal is to defend your eligibility so you keep every penny you're legally entitled to.</p>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>How long does the IRS have to audit my claim?<span>&#8595;</span></summary>
                <p class="faq-answer">The IRS generally has 5 years from the date of filing. For most 2020/2021 claims, audits can occur through 2025-2027.</p>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>What does the free case review include?<span>&#8595;</span></summary>
                <p class="faq-answer">We analyze your original ERC filing, identify vulnerabilities, assess your risk level, and provide recommendations &mdash; all confidentially with no obligation.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

